        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. As to the Judge, the Son of man, him whom you now see in the shape of a man, and whom men vilify and contemn under that notion. He is to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Judge of quick and dead, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Acts 10:42 2 Timothy 4:1",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Acts 10:42",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Timothy 4:1",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. As to the splendour of it. He shall ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "come in the glory of his Father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It is also his glory, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John 17:5",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 17:5",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; he calls it the glory of his Father, because by his eternal generation he received it together with the Divine nature from his Father, and it was common to him with his Father; or because his commission for judgment was from his Father: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For the Father judgeth no man, but hath committed all judgment unto the Son, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " John 5:22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
