  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 16:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Μέλλει ἔρχεσθαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "is about to come",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") A stronger expression than ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐλεύσεται",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "will come",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As the teaching concerning the person of Christ is immediately followed by that concerning His Cross, so is the latter by that concerning His glory.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τότε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "then",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") All things are put off till then.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀποδώσει ἑκάστῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "He will render to each individual",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This is the attribute of Divine Majesty; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 2:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".[770]—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πρᾶξιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "action, conduct, doing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The word is put in the singular, for the whole life of man is one ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "doing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".[771]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
