  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 27.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For the Son of man shall come.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The final judgment would put things in their true light - would show the value of self-sacrifice, would reveal the punishment of self-pleasing. Our Lord seems to refer to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Daniel 7:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as it were, in testimony to the truth of what he had just said. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Shall come",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "μέλλει ἔρχεσθαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "venturus est",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Vulgate), is more than the bare announcement, and implies that it is in accordance with the eternal counsels of God that he should appear this second time. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "In the glory of his Father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " As one with the Father, and his Representative. So he speaks of \"the glory which thou hast given me\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 17:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Reward",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀποδώσει",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "render, reddet",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Vulgate). The term includes punishment as well as recompense. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Works",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "πρᾶξιν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "doing, work.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The word does not signify isolated acts, but general course of conduct, practice as a whole. Matthew 16:27",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
